description.plain: The New Jersey-born and Los Angeles-based singer and songwriter made her debut as an artist with the intoxicating “Red Wine.” Right out of the gate, it claimed coveted real estate on playlists such as Spotify’s New Music Friday and Fresh Finds: Pop. It lit up TikTok with hundreds of thousands of views and even caught the attention of Victoria Justice and the legendary Gwen Stefani who shared it on an Instagram story.

description.plain:
“Sweet Endless Xylophones” is an unreleased song intended for Addison Rae.

Despite being co-written by the singer, Addison never (knowingly) recorded vocals for the track. However, a demo labeled as “2.0” and sung by co-writer Tia Tia was leaked online in August of 2022.
